The paper deals with graph drawing algorithms and their relations to various graph classes, which are typical topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DM, cs.GT). The use of right-angle crossings and few bends in the drawings suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of graph drawing and layout (cs.SI). The study of beyond-planar graphs, such as 1-planar, IC-planar, and NIC-planar graphs, involves combinatorial and structural aspects of graphs, which are also relevant to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
